summary: Cornholio4 here and I am surprised to see a big Spideybug shipper like me, I think I helped stat the ship, if you want I got a...
question: Cornholio4 here and I am surprised to see a big Spideybug shipper like me, I think I helped stat the ship, if you want I got a bunch of stories of the ship on my account (shameless plug sorry) if you want to tell em what you think please, also I liked your moral dues story
answer:
I’ve actually read them beforehand. They’re pretty neat, though, they do jump the gun a little.

Your stories tend to start post-their relationship beginning, and while that does give readers a look at the ship, it doesn’t give them the opportunity to acclimate to it. We don’t get to sit along and watch two dorks tiptoe around each other and fall in love. There’s no awkward flirting, back tracking, or cute moments when they fall forward and jerk back before they do something they think they’ll regret.

Not that your stories aren’t good, but there’s a certain modicum of depth that you should try exploring. It’d be fun to see them do more than deal with the narrative’s central conflict. Focus a bit on the romance and the trials of being a couple.

I mean, after I read your stories, I drew up a skeleton plot of how SpideyBug would happen for me. Starting with Marinette’s parents taking her on a vacation out of France to NYC to escape her school life, then progressing to her first meeting with the YouTube famous Spider-Man when they both show up at the scene of a crime as their superhero personas. Then, meeting each other in their civilian identities immediately afterwards when Marinette de-transforms in the same alley that Peter is undressing in. As the story progressed, they met up a few more times while fighting crime in NYC, with Peter doing his civic duty, much to his Aunt May’s frustration and concerns, and Marinette scratching that itch for heroism, which Sabine is proud of. (Her mom knows, and so does her dad) Later, Marinette goes back to Paris, leaving on friendly terms, but Peter is miserable now that his crush is gone.

Tony, the Invincible Iron Dad, notices and makes him confess his feelings. Then, being as supportive as he can be, takes his “intern” to visit the French branch of Stark Industries in Paris, France.

When I posted about the Miraculous MCU, I took ideas from my original plot and weaved them into the overall arc. So, eventually, you’ll be seeing some SpideyBug on your dashes.

Are we not gonna talk about how none of Peter’s classmates aged in five years? Because as we saw with Scott’s daughter, those five years after the snap weren’t erased. Peter’s friends absolutely should be in college right now. How is Marvel supposed to explain that away?

summary: Are we not even going to talk about how all the Tony Stark memorials in the FFH trailer are Iron Man based? Everyone’s pushing...
body:
Are we not even going to talk about how all the Tony Stark memorials in the FFH trailer are Iron Man based? Everyone’s pushing Peter into stepping up his hero game (be the next Iron Man, i.e. sacrifice whatever it takes to finish the mission) when Tony was the only one who wanted him to be a kid a little longer (stick close to the ground).

Everyone’s looking at those Iron Man memorials and sees the hero who did his job; Peter looks and see’s the mentor who died to get him back.

body:
ALSO???? the whole multiverse thing????? HOLY SHIT!!!!!! if quentin beck is telling the truth abt where he’s from (and i mean, its mysterio so i wouldnt be surprised if its a lie) then that opens up SO many possibilities for future movies????? like. what if we got an mcu miles morales (and i know he already exists in the mcu but hes not spiderman in that universe (yet)) or spider gwen!!! HOW COOL would an MCU SPIDER GWEN BE!! or like. any of the multiverse characters. oh my god. i know they probably wont do anything like this cause into the spiderverse has already done that but like. WHAT IF. also i just wanna say i love how the introduction to the multiverse (if mysterio is telling the truth) is in a spiderman movie (cause ofc it is djksfdhjg) 

also, did u guys know, the mcu actually exists in the marvel comics multiverse!!! its earth-199999!!! so if the multiverse is gonna be a thing in this movie, TECHNICALLY there are crossover possibilities with all the comics universes. and i know theyre not going to actually do that, but like!! they’re canonically in the same multiverse and in the comics there is definitely universe crossing tech… so like. im gonna go daydream abt that.
